text: Tribune is a city in the U.S. state of Kansas. It is the county seat of Greeley County. As of the 2020 census, the population of the city was 772. ==History== The town was founded in 1886. It became the county seat one year later in 1887. ==Education== The city has 3 schools in total: 1 Elementary, 1 Middle, and 1 High School. == References == Category:County seats in Kansas Category:Cities in Kansas
title: Tribune, Kansas
